magnetic field-- the force of

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:13.270
it, the force that's affecting
the circuit-- is pushing

00:02:13.270 --> 00:02:14.160
straight up.

00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:17.080
So there's no longer any net
torque because the force is

00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:19.720
pushing straight up and that
moment arm distance-- this

00:02:19.720 --> 00:02:22.460
distance-- is now also
pointing straight up.

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:25.700
And torque is also a cross
product, so you actually care

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:28.080
about the perpendicular
forces.

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:30.890
So there, at this vertical
point, there's no net torque.

00:02:30.890 --> 00:02:33.340
And the same is true at the
bottom of the circuit.

00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:36.160
Because at the bottom the
magnetic field force is going

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:38.940
