00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:14.760
And it had done it all the way
to the point where we had

00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:17.800
rotated more than 90 degrees,
but now all of a sudden the

00:05:17.800 --> 00:05:21.560
net force through the magnetic
field was going to reverse.

00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:24.610
Because the side that has a
current going upwards is now

00:05:24.610 --> 00:05:26.360
the left hand side.

00:05:26.360 --> 00:05:28.830
So now the force from the
magnetic field is out on this

00:05:28.830 --> 00:05:31.660
side and you're going
to want to rotate in

00:05:31.660 --> 00:05:34.160
the opposite direction.

00:05:34.160 --> 00:05:34.970
Hopefully that makes sense.

00:05:34.970 --> 00:05:35.850
Just think about what happens.

00:05:35.850 --> 00:05:38.380
Visualize this coil rotating.

